#compdef toon
# =============================================================================
# toon — Token-Oriented Object Notation (TOON) — a compact,
#         human-readable, schema-aware data format optimized for
#         LLM PROMPT TOKEN EFFICIENCY.  TOON encodes structured
#         data (objects, arrays, primitives — the same domain
#         as JSON) but using significantly FEWER TOKENS when
#         processed by modern LLM tokenizers (GPT-4/Claude/
#         Gemini tokenization grids).  Typical token savings:
#         30-60% versus JSON for the same logical content,
#         depending on schema regularity.
#
#         Distinguishing TOON features:
#           - INDENTATION + KEY-VALUE syntax (YAML-like surface)
#           - Delimited array shorthand: `colors: red,green,blue`
#             vs JSON's `"colors": ["red","green","blue"]`
#           - SCHEMA-AWARE row encoding: `users[N]{id,name}:`
#             header followed by N delimited rows
#           - Three configurable array delimiters: `,` (default),
#             `\t` (tab — best for LLM tokens), `|` (pipe — best
#             for human readability)
#           - Optional KEY FOLDING: collapse `parent.child.leaf`
#             paths into single keys for further token savings
#           - LOSSLESS round-trip: encode JSON → TOON → JSON
#             yields identical data
#         The `toon` CLI converts between JSON and TOON formats,
#         supports stdin/stdout streaming for shell pipelines,
#         and emits token statistics for direct comparison
#         against the source JSON.  Distributed by the toon-
#         format project at toonformat.dev.
#
# Author:  toon-format community — TOON spec + reference
#          implementations + CLI co-developed by independent
#          contributors focused on LLM-prompt-engineering
#          optimization.  Reference implementation in
#          TypeScript; ports to Python, Go, Rust, and other
#          languages are emerging.
# Source:  https://github.com/toon-format/toon
#          https://github.com/toon-format/toon/blob/main/packages/cli/src/index.ts
# CLI:     packages/cli/src/index.ts — uses `citty` (unjs's
#          argv parser, already documented in taxonomy) for
#          subcommand routing.  Headline output library:
#          `consola` (unjs's unified logger) for status +
#          error + statistics rendering throughout the
#          encode/decode pipeline.
# Library: consola
#          ("Elegant Console Logger for Node.js and Browser" —
#           unjs/Nuxt collective — released 2017 by Pooya
#           Parsa et al as the unified logging library for the
#           Nuxt.js framework, then spun out as a standalone
#           library used by the entire unjs ecosystem (nuxt,
#           nitro, h3, ofetch, ohash, ufo, unbuild, vite-node,
#           and dozens of other unjs+Nuxt-adjacent projects).
#           consola unifies what other ecosystems split across
#           multiple libraries: LOG LEVELS (silent/fatal/error/
#           warn/info/success/debug/trace) + COLORED OUTPUT +
#           STRUCTURED ERROR FORMATTING + SPINNERS via cli-
#           spinners + PROMPTS via @clack/prompts integration +
#           PROGRESS REPORTING + REPORTER ABSTRACTION (custom
#           output backends like JSON-lines, Fancy-TUI,
#           Browser-DevTools).)
# License: MIT (toon); MIT (consola)
# Status:  toon — 24437+ stars on toon-format/toon (top-200 GH
#          project; explosive growth Q4 2025 + Q1 2026 due to
#          LLM-prompt-engineering use cases); consola — 7800+
#          stars on unjs/consola, foundational dependency of
#          ~200+ unjs/nuxt-ecosystem packages with 50M+ weekly
#          npm downloads.
#
